### 1. Batch Reads and Writes
Batching reads and writes can significantly reduce the number of network calls to Firestore, improving performance.

### 2. Minimize Redundant Reads
Avoid reading the same document multiple times. Cache data locally if it will be used multiple times within the function.

### 3. Optimize Roster Handling
Instead of fetching and copying each roster individually, consider fetching all necessary rosters in a single batch read.

### 4. Use Transactions for Atomic Operations
Use Firestore transactions where possible to ensure atomicity and reduce the number of separate read/write operations.

### 5. Efficient Data Structures
Use efficient data structures like maps and sets to handle lookups and updates efficiently.

